<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1936,2034]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,152,287]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">
The RBINS kindly provided four 
<typeStatus box="[532,630,1936,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" box="[669,969,1936,1962]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ducalis">
<emphasis box="[669,879,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Hydrochus ducalis</emphasis>
Knisch
</taxonomicName>
, which are part of the Orchymont/Knisch types collection. All four 
<typeStatus box="[450,548,1972,1998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">syntypes</typeStatus>
are conspecific males. I have selected one to serve as 
<typeStatus box="[1192,1295,1972,1998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">lectotype</typeStatus>
and labeled it as such, and provide images of the habitus, male genitalia, and labels of this specimen (
<figureCitation box="[1193,1275,2008,2034]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1780,1805]" captionTargetBox="[166,1432,326,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,309,1755]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hydrochus ducalis Knisch, habitus and male genitalia of lectotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557935/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1289,1341,2008,2034]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1980,2005]" captionTargetBox="[215,1415,381,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[158,1430,381,1955]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 12A–E. Labels of lectotypes. (A) Hydrochus ducalis Knisch; (B) Hydrochus drakei Knisch; (C) Hydrochus variabilis Knisch; (D) Hydrochus corruscans Bruch; (E) Hydrochus argutus Knisch." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557951/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">12A</figureCitation>
). Lecto- 
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="155" type="description">
type labels (
<figureCitation box="[291,397,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1980,2005]" captionTargetBox="[215,1415,381,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[158,1430,381,1955]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 12A–E. Labels of lectotypes. (A) Hydrochus ducalis Knisch; (B) Hydrochus drakei Knisch; (C) Hydrochus variabilis Knisch; (D) Hydrochus corruscans Bruch; (E) Hydrochus argutus Knisch." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557951/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
): “Bras.Corumba [Matto Grosso] // Coll. A.Kniž COTYPUS // det. Kniž 
<taxonomicName box="[1236,1317,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ducalis">
<emphasis box="[1236,1317,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">ducalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. // coll. A.d’Orchymont: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[343,465,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[343,465,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Hydrochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R.M.H.N.B. 15.962 // HABITUS/GENIT. DIGITAL IMAGES captured 2019 P.D. Perkins // [red] 
<typeStatus box="[289,449,225,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" box="[456,752,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ducalis">
<emphasis box="[456,666,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Hydrochus ducalis</emphasis>
Knisch
</taxonomicName>
desig. P. D. Perkins.” The three non-lectotype 
<typeStatus box="[1278,1376,225,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">syntypes</typeStatus>
have been labeled 
<typeStatus box="[299,464,261,287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
