<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="156" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1851,2022]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,153,251]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="156" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1852,1878]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Remarks.</emphasis>
One of the male 
<typeStatus box="[503,665,1851,1877]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
has a distinctly more ovoid basal piece, while the structures of the aedeagus and the parameres do not significantly differ from those of the 
<typeStatus box="[938,1044,1887,1913]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">lectotype</typeStatus>
. Images of this specimen are given as an example of some of the infraspecific variation to be expected in species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[1065,1187,1923,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1065,1187,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Hydrochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1203,1272,1922,1949]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1550,1575]" captionTargetBox="[172,1435,309,1510]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,273,1525]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hydrochus ducalis Knisch, habitus and male genitalia of paralectotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557937" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557937/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The drawing of 
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" box="[184,484,1959,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ducalis">
<emphasis box="[184,396,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Hydrochus ducalis</emphasis>
Knisch
</taxonomicName>
male genitalia by 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A." box="[701,847,1959,1985]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" pagination="87 - 104" refId="ref6088" refString="Oliva, A. (1992) The species of Hydrochus (Coleoptera; Hydrophiloidea; Hydrochidae) described from South America. Bulletin et annales de la Societe royale belge d'entomologie, 128, 87 - 104." type="journal article" year="1992">Oliva (1992)</bibRefCitation>
is unfortunately very inaccurate in several aspects, including general proportions, shapes of the parameres, size of the basal piece, etc. I have also examined the holo- type of 
<taxonomicName authority="Makhan 1992" authorityName="Makhan" authorityYear="1992" box="[235,632,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desenderi">
<emphasis box="[235,472,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">Hydrochus desenderi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Makhan, D." box="[478,632,153,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" pagination="95 - 103" refId="ref5661" refString="Makhan, D. (1992) Twelve new Hydrochus - species from South America. Phegea, 20 (2), 95 - 103." type="journal article" year="1992">Makhan 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(which is one of the 
<typeStatus box="[864,962,153,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[998,1207,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ducalis">
<emphasis box="[998,1207,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">Hydrochus ducalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), including the male genitalia. I concur with 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A." box="[419,564,189,216]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" pagination="301 - 341" refId="ref6127" refString="Oliva, A. (1996) The genus Hydrochus Leach (Coleoptera: Hydrophiloidea: Hydrochidae) in South America, with special reference to Argentina. Bulletin et annales de la Societe royale belge d'entomologie, 132, 301 - 341." type="journal article" year="1996">Oliva (1996)</bibRefCitation>
that 
<taxonomicName authority="Makhan" authorityName="Makhan" authorityYear="1992" box="[620,958,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desenderi">
<emphasis box="[620,859,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">Hydrochus desenderi</emphasis>
Makhan
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch. The" authorityName="Knisch. The" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ducalis">
<emphasis box="[1226,1436,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">Hydrochus ducalis</emphasis>
Knisch. The
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[295,393,225,251]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Makhan" authorityName="Makhan" authorityYear="1992" box="[430,675,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desenderi">
<emphasis box="[430,573,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">H. desenderi</emphasis>
Makhan
</taxonomicName>
, deposited in the RBINS, has the same label data as the 
<typeStatus box="[1303,1409,225,251]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
